<PB REF="011837_0819_0F9D899B6DDEA148">
powers in Europe&mdash;The mo&s;t con&s;iderable revolution of the &s;ixteenth century in the court of Rome&mdash;The general revolt again&s;t the doctrines of the church of Rome, and the power of the Popes&mdash;This abridged the extent of the Pope's dominions,&mdash;and obliged them to change the &s;pirit of their government&mdash;The Reformation contributed to improve the church both in &s;cience and morals&mdash;The effects of it extend to the characters of the Popes them&s;elves&mdash;State of the re|public of Venice&mdash;Of Tu&s;cany&mdash;Of the Dukes of Savoy&mdash; Of the United Provinces&mdash;Of Ru&s;&s;ia&mdash;Of Denmark and Sweden.</P>
